This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with learning distributed representations for relation instances, which is a central technique in downstream NLP applications. Additionally, the paper discusses different encoders including RNN, LSTM, and GRU, which are commonly used in NLP tasks. 

The paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with enhancing the performance of distributed representations for relation classification, which is a common task in AI. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses different techniques for composing distributed representations, which is a core concept in machine learning. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with similarity ratings for relational patterns, which is a common concept in information retrieval. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses different neural network architectures for composing distributed representations.
